===Series 4 (2015)=== The series had four episodes:
{{Episode table |background=#C39200 |overall= |series= |title= |aux1= |airdate= |country=UK |aux1T= Produced and directed by |episodes= {{Episode list | EpisodeNumber = 12 | EpisodeNumber2 = 1 | Title = L S Lowry | DirectedBy = Rachel Jardine<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.radiotimes.com/episode/dn7xsx/fake-or-fortune--series-4---1-lowry|title=Series 4, Episode 1 |publisher=[[Radio Times]]|accessdate=21 August 2017}}</ref> | OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2015|07|05|df=yes}} | ShortSummary = Experts determined whether three works - ''Lady with Dogs'', ''Darby and Joan'' and ''Crowd Scene'' - were genuine paintings by [[L. S. Lowry]] or forgeries. They had been bought in the 1960s by a Cheshire businessman, Gerald Ames. Lowry was described as "probably the most faked British artist, his deceptively simple style of painting making him a soft target for forgers." Experts analysed the paint used in one of the paintings, but the white paint did not match the flake white Lowry claimed to have always used. Lowry claimed to have only used five colours, [[White lead|flake white (lead white)]], [[ivory black]], [[Vermilion|vermillion red]], [[Prussian blue]] and [[yellow ochre]], produced by [[Winsor & Newton]]. Photographic evidence from the 1950s, however, showed that he had experimented with both [[titanium white]] and [[zinc white]]: ''Darby and Joan'' contained traces of zinc white. The same painting was also plainly visible in a contemporary BBC documentary film.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/iplayer/episode/b0612kxh/fake-or-fortune-series-4-1-lowry |title=BBC iPlayer - Fake or Fortune? - Series 4: 1. Lowry |publisher=Bbc.co.uk |date=5 July 2015|accessdate=5 July 2015}}</ref>
